author: stefan2
msg: Yet another server-side tool: it crawls through your format 4+
FSFS repository and prints data size & count stats.
This is the initial commit based on a copy of fsfs-reorg for
its FSFS structure reading and online representation code.
Lots of more info such as histograms, per file-type info etc
will be added in the future.
Not really sure where I want to go with that but for now, it
helps me verifying my assumptions on which data or structures
is dominant in FSFS repositories etc.  Since all access is
read-only, it should be safe to use but it still requires a
lot of memory.  Also not sure whether that's going to be a
long-term supported tool.
* build.conf
(__ALL_TESTS__): add fsfs-stats dependency
(fsfs-stats): new target / project section
* tools/server-side/fsfs-stats.c
() new tool sources
